- `this`
- property lookup
- prototype behavior
- slow paths

## The Main Lesson

Object pointers give you heap identity.

`this`, prototypes, and shapes give that object model operational meaning.

They explain why property access is dynamic, and also why it can still become fast with guards and stable structure.

The next chapter looks at garbage collection, which is what keeps all these heap objects alive and safe while JIT code runs.
